comments.content:
Hi,  
That's a really good one - it's part of the Partizan Belgrade Soccer Team logo.  
I would imagine that it's a custom job that only consists of those letters and not available as a regular font.

Anyhow if you require scalable vectors of the complete logo then get my .eps version from here:  
 [https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.eps](http://web.archive.org/web/20140606123654/https:/dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.eps "https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.eps")  
or if you want it here's a pdf copy:  
 [https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.pdf](http://web.archive.org/web/20140606123654/https:/dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.pdf "https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/37241705/PartizanBelgrade.pdf")

It reminds me those crazy neon fonts in the old Letraset catalogue, Oxford, Uptight Neon, Yagi Link Double etc., but check out:  
 [http://bowfinprintworks.com/LinedFontGuide03.html](http://web.archive.org/web/20140606123654/http:/bowfinprintworks.com/LinedFontGuide03.html "http://bowfinprintworks.com/LinedFontGuide03.html")  
where you may find something similar (or maybe not)  
Good Hunting.

Regards  
Doghouse Studio
